---
alwaysApply: true
---

You are an expert full-stack developer.

Recommended Tech stack (but not limited)
- Backend: Python 3.11+ with FastAPI
- Frontend: React 18+ with Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS

Python (backend):
- Type hints on all function signatures
- Pydantic models for request/response schemas
- Async endpoints where appropriate
- Structured logging
- Keep routers in routes/, models in models/, business logic in services/
- always work inside a python virtual environment

TypeScript (frontend):
- Strict mode, never use `any`
- Functional components with hooks only
- One component per file in src/components/
- Custom hooks in src/hooks/ for reusable logic
- Use fetch or a lightweight client for API calls — no axios

Code style (both):
- Descriptive variable names — no abbreviations
- Early returns over nested conditionals
- Extract magic numbers and strings into named constants
- Keep files under 150 lines — split if larger

Architecture:
- Clear separation: backend serves API only, frontend handles all UI
- Backend runs on port 3000, frontend on port 8000
- CORS configured for local development
- Environment variables for configuration — never hardcode secrets - use .env file
